    <p>While I love gold and silver as much as the next guy (I own more than ten thousand dollars worth of each), they're just not practical as currencies.&nbsp; They are magnificent ways to store large sums of value long-term.&nbsp; But for day-to-day purchases, and moving money outside of borders (and outside the watchful eye of government agents), Bitcoin wins.&nbsp;</p>
<p>I can use Bitcoin to transfer money to anyone in the world instantly and anonymously.&nbsp; I can store millions of dollars in a sentence that I've memorized.&nbsp; Try to confiscate that, TSA.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="links"><ul class="links"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
