    <p>+1 however, due to the hashing algorithm the transaction history is verified in time-forward manner only. It's exceedingly difficult to tamper with the transaction series to produce a new one but it's impossible to reverse backwards to find specific transactions.</p>
<p>As for 'origins' it doesn't matter: if it doesn't work, don't use it. It's open-source so its origins are less important than its current abilities and limitations (that are many)</p>

